## Context

Two problems:

### 1. Null model is too weak

`run_l3_permutations` shuffles the 25-year time series of burst counts —
it only asks "is this series of summary statistics non-uniform?"  The
correct null is: "could these burst counts arise from random document-to-
year assignment?"

Every other method shuffles the underlying pool documents and recomputes
the statistic.  L3 should do the same: randomly reassign all corpus
documents to years (preserving year sizes), recompute TF-IDF burst counts
per permuted year, repeat n_perm times.

This is tractable: precompute the full term-document TF-IDF matrix once,
then for each permutation shuffle the document-to-year assignment vector
and recount bursts.  O(V × n_perm) with no re-fitting of the vectorizer.

### 2. Plot uses Z-scores; should use raw burst counts

Consistent with ticket 0113 (drop Z-score rescaling, plot raw values),
the L3 axis should show raw burst counts per year, not crossyear Z-scores.
Currently `run_l3_permutations` stores Z-scores in the `observed` column
— it should store raw burst counts instead.

### 3. Ribbon not drawn

`plot_zoo_results.py` filters for `window=="3"` when looking for null data.
L3 only has `window="0"` → ribbon never shown.

## Relevant files

- `scripts/_permutation_lexical.py:40` — `run_l3_permutations` — rewrite
  to shuffle documents rather than summary statistics; output raw counts
- `scripts/plot_zoo_results.py:137` — `w3_null` filter — extend to also
  handle `window=="0"` for the non-sliding axis
- `scripts/plot_zoo_results.py:196` — non-sliding axis plot — switch from
  `z_score` to `value` column (per ticket 0113)

## Actions

1. Rewrite `run_l3_permutations` in `_permutation_lexical.py`:
   - Load full corpus texts and fit global TF-IDF vectorizer (as now).
   - For each permutation: shuffle the document-year assignment (preserve
     per-year counts), recompute burst count per year using the shuffled
     assignment, store as null statistic.
   - Store raw burst count (not Z-score) in the `observed` column.
   - Output `null_mean`, `null_std` as mean/std of raw burst counts across
     permutations.

2. In `plot_zoo_results.py`, extend ribbon logic to check `window=="0"`:
   ```python
   w0_null = null_df[null_df["window"] == "0"] if null_df is not None else None
   ```
   Draw `fill_between(year, null_mean − 1.96*null_std, null_mean + 1.96*null_std)`
   on the non-sliding axis when `w0_null` is available.

3. Non-sliding axis already plots `value` after ticket 0113 lands; ensure
   L3's `tab_crossyear_L3.csv` `value` column is raw burst counts (it
   already is — the Z-score column is separate).

4. Re-run `make content/tables/tab_null_L3.csv` and rebuild zoo figure.

## Test

Red: add a test that (a) calls the new `run_l3_permutations` on a tiny
fixture (5 years, 20 docs each, random texts) and asserts `observed`
values are integers (raw burst counts), and (b) asserts null_mean and
null_std are in the same scale as observed (not Z-score scale).

## Verification

- [ ] `tab_null_L3.csv` `observed` column contains raw burst counts
  matching `tab_div_L3.csv` `value` for the same years
- [ ] L3 zoo figure shows raw burst-count axis with time-varying ribbon
- [ ] `make check-fast` passes

## Invariants

- The full TF-IDF vectorizer is fitted once per permutation run (not
  per permutation) — same as the divergence computation.
- Year sizes (documents per year) are preserved in the shuffle.

## Exit criteria

- `run_l3_permutations` shuffles documents, outputs raw counts
- L3 figure shows ribbon in raw units
- PR merged
